results.name: Number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons, C_(2h) symmetry and containing n carbon atoms.
reference: G. Brinkmann, G. Caporossi and P. Hansen, "A Survey and New Results on Computer Enumeration of Polyhex and Fusene Hydrocarbons", J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 43 (2003) pp. 842-851. See Table 5 column 6 on page 847.
example: If n=62 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 2.
If n=64 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 32.
If n=66 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 138.
If n=68 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 510.
If n=90 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 232842.
